Class NetId

Namespace
Nebula
Assembly
Nebula.dll

A unique identifier for a networked object. The NetId for a node is different between the server and client. On the client side, a NetId is only a byte, whereas on the server side it is an int64. The server's WorldRunner keeps a map of all NetIds to their corresponding value on each client for serialization.
